data.title: called 90s Band
data.meta_description: My so-called 90s Band is a ragtag group of professionals from western Pennsylvania, hellbent on raising the roof in the grandest tradition of bands like Weezer, Foo Fighters, and those memorable singles by bands with forgettable names. Some call it a party, some call it fun; whatever the name, it's
data.text:
“Your participation in our 30th-anniversary celebration event was crucial in making the ULTIMATE 90's afterparty a success!

Established in 1994, when we decided to host a 90's afterparty, reaching out to you was our immediate choice.

Your involvement was greatly appreciated by our attendees, and we are grateful for your flexibility in providing music for our fantastic drone show. We eagerly look forward to welcoming you back!”

“My wife wanted a memorable birthday, she was throwing a Lisa frank themed party. I was at a loss for what to add till I found the band’s web page.

They were prompt courteous and professional during the whole experience.

They dealt with my bulldog trying to intimidate the bass drum, and when Lieutenant realized he wasn’t going to win. They took his effort to run off with the mic inside. They set up quietly, asked the right questions and prompted a setup I never thought of. That setup ended up being great allowing for the party and my neighbors to enjoy the band.

They set up the sound and music levels so as to be heard throughout the house and backyard but not loud enough to prevent socializing while in the next room.

I can’t express the professionalism and how easy they made hiring them was. 10 out of 10 will hire again”

“Saw them tonight at the Science Center and my 5 year old requested Spice Girls and Christina Aguilera which they rocked out too! Thanks so much for making her happy! You guys were awesome to watch and can't wait to see you again!”
